This idea has shaped our understanding of history, philosophy, and literature, as well as influencing areas such as existentialism and postmodernism.

These are just some of the many ideas that continue to shape modern culture and thought in the 21st century. It is important to note that Nietzsche's ideas were controversial during his lifetime, but he continues to inspire debate and discussion today.

When someone is vaccinated, they receive a small amount of the infection or disease in the form of an inactive or dead version, which triggers an immune response in the body. The immune system then remembers the infection or disease and can quickly and effectively fight it off if they come into contact with it in the future.

Flokkimmunitet is a concept that describes the immunity of a large group of people. It refers to the immune system's ability to protect against an infectious disease when a significant portion of the population has been vaccinated against it. It works by creating a "herd immunity" effect, where enough people are immune to an infectious disease that it cannot spread easily through the population. This makes it much less likely that someone will contract an infectious disease, even if they are exposed to it.
